        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>280</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>105900</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63308"><name nymRef="#Ἀστυκλῆς">Ἀστυκλῆς</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65111"><name nymRef="#Νίκαιος" type="patronymic">Νικαίω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Astyklès fils de Nikaios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Astykles son of Nikaios.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Astykles figlio di Nikaios.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This stele had been brought to the garden of Casa Parisi before 1960. It was probably not found before World War II, but brought there for protection 
                in post-war times, when Goodchild was in charge of the Deparment of Antiquities.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
